1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,228
Three days into the desert, Leila finally stopped running.

2
00:00:03,228 --> 00:00:06,722
She knelt before Malik and placed a small clay vial into his hands.

3
00:00:06,722 --> 00:00:11,029
This is not medicine, she said. It is not for hunger, or thirst, or fear.

4
00:00:11,029 --> 00:00:13,282
Then what is it for, Malik asked.

5
00:00:13,282 --> 00:00:20,422
For the one moment you stand between life and death. Only that moment. Not before. Not for pride. Not for anger.

6
00:00:20,422 --> 00:00:22,930
Malik did not understand. Not yet.

7
00:00:22,930 --> 00:00:27,283
But he held the vial the way his mother held her fear: carefully, and in silence.

8
00:00:27,283 --> 00:00:30,720
Warrior of the Sand Dunes continues. Original fiction.
